sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM participants WHERE consent_form_signed = 1) AS total_participants,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM access_logs) AS total_access_logs;

external_knowledge:
- "lanterns" metaphorically refers to "experiments";
- "hall of 2023" refers to the time frame of experiments started between '2023-01-01' and '2023-12-31';
- "wise keepers" refers to "researchers";
- "gazed upon them more than ten times" refers to "total accesses > 10";
- "each gaze being a fleeting glimpse or a deep, pondering stare" refers to the average duration of the access, which could be short or long.

Engaged individuals: Those who have interactions lasting more than 60 seconds;
Meaningful exchanges: Interactions with a duration greater than 60 seconds; 
Frequency: Number of interactions;
Duration details: Total interaction time, average interaction time, shortest and longest interaction time.

