SELECT researchers.researcher_name
FROM researchers
WHERE researchers.researcher_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT experiments.principal_investigator_id
    FROM experiments
) AND researchers.researcher_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT access_logs.researcher_id
    FROM access_logs
);

external_knowledge:
- "shadow in the crowd" metaphorically refers to a participant who stands out due to their low level of engagement; 
- "barely glimpsing the stage" implies someone who has interacted minimally with the content or activities;
- "lightest footprint of views" is a metaphorical way to describe the participant with the least number of 'view' interactions.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT trials.trial_id) AS unique_trial_count
FROM experiments
INNER JOIN trials ON experiments.experiment_id = trials.experiment_id;

SELECT DISTINCT researchers.researcher_name
FROM researchers
INNER JOIN access_logs ON researchers.researcher_id = access_logs.researcher_id;

